
# It's a good idea to explain:
#
# * The reason behind doing this commit.
# * Your approach to this implementation.
# * Side effects and things to look for.
# * Reference to github issues.
#
# feat:     New feature for the user.
# fix:      Bug fix for the user.
# docs:     Documentation changes.
# style:    Formatting, linting, etc. No production code change.
# refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature.
# test:     adding missing tests or refactoring them.
# perf      Performance improvements.
# chore     Other changes that don't modify source or test files
# build     Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies.
# ci        Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts.
# revert    Reverts a previous commit.
